In 2020, we visited San Miguel de Allende and fell in love. The town kind of reminded me of home, except it was magical in a way I had never experienced before. The easiest decision of my life was choosing it as the setting for my very special day. 

We chose to get married early in November during Dia de Los Muertos and built a traditional altar with ofrendas so that we and all of our wedding guests could celebrate the lives of loved ones who are no longer with us, like my Lola. I felt her presence there with me every day and now I’m in tears as I say goodbye to the most extraordinary month of my life 🤍

I feel so lucky to have found the best wedding planner, too. @yulianaweddingplanner thank you for making my vision and wildest dreams come to life, for being so sweet, levelheaded, patient, talented and assertive every step of the way. Every girl deserves a planner and a friend like you.

She’s a wife, y’allllll 🥹👰🏽‍♀️🎉🎆

There’s something so fun about getting my hair and makeup done for work but nothing feels as good as peeling those lashes off at the end of a long day😂 Over the years I’ve learned to love both the glam and the feeling of my fresh and clean face. Just a reminder that amazing things start to happen when you wake up in the morning and love the person in the mirror🤍 Beauty comes in every shape, color, size and style ✨ 
Also this glam session was lifeeee🤍
Last day of school was awesome 😌
Chao 2023🥹 oh & big shout out to my traveling buddy, Pollito—thanks for holding all the good and bad tears. What a year we’ve had together!
